cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

This paper is about deep learning models and their optimization for deployment in resource-limited environments. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses pruning methods, which are commonly used in neural network compression, suggesting cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible category. Finally, the paper uses ensemble learning, which is a technique used in data science and machine learning, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as a possible category.
